				<h1 class="mb-0" style="font-family:monospace ">Welcome</h1>
				<h2 class="mb-100 title-border-lg" style="font-family: monospace">to the  <i>Code Cat Blog!</i></h2>
				<p class="mb-80 mr-5">
					Hey there!
					My name is Angelica Velez.<br />
					I am a junior developer located in Chattanooga, TN - 4 years married and have 3 beautiful cats! Since I'm a crazy cat lady,
					I can't help but let it flow a bit into all aspects of life, hence the title, The Code Cat Blog! 
					Most likely, I won't speak much on cat science, though I'm sure it'll slip in here and there (maybe my 
					fur babies will make a cameo every once in a while). <br />
					My main focus with this blog will be to detail my mental journey through learning to code.
					This includes crazy late night epiphanies, breaking personal barriers, discussing resources 
					and research in becoming a programmer and all the tidbits that surface along the way! <br />
					I'm looking forward to sharing this journey with you and I hope you find some comfort in knowing 
					you have someone else out there who also feels like they're risking all their nine lives trying to 
					learn a new skill and change careers! It's not easy, but it is simple, let's get to coding! :) 

				</p>
